WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:03.601
We're in the exact spot where
she heard something scream.

00:03.603 --> 00:05.337
And something
just screamed at us.

00:05.339 --> 00:09.074
They didn't get to finish
their life and they're angry.

00:09.076 --> 00:11.343
CHIP:
This man killed people.

00:11.345 --> 00:13.344
He said, "No!"

00:13.346 --> 00:15.414
This guy's ready to rumble.

00:15.416 --> 00:18.149
Can you stop
turning off my equipment?

00:18.151 --> 00:20.418
I [bleep] saw somebody
stand in that hallway.

00:20.420 --> 00:22.888
That [bleep] is rare.

00:22.890 --> 00:24.089
He's coming here.

00:24.091 --> 00:26.558
Just letting you know
he wants nothing to do with you.

00:26.560 --> 00:28.227
♪♪

00:28.229 --> 00:30.028
[ Crows cawing ]

00:30.030 --> 00:33.632
BRUNI: When the dead are
forgotten, they become restless.

00:33.634 --> 00:35.900
Oh, my God!
You just touched me.
What? I did not touch you.

00:35.902 --> 00:37.503
I'm Amy Bruni.

00:37.505 --> 00:40.772
A haunting encounter
redefined my life.

00:40.774 --> 00:44.175
I live with that experience
and seek answers to the unknown.

00:44.177 --> 00:46.178
It says, "I am."

00:46.180 --> 00:47.913
I'm Adam Berry.

00:47.915 --> 00:51.183
At Gettysburg, the shadows
and screams of dead soldiers

00:51.185 --> 00:53.452
turned me into
a supernatural believer.

00:53.454 --> 00:54.920
Oh, my God.

00:54.922 --> 00:58.123
Together, our investigations
bring peace to the living...

00:58.125 --> 01:00.258
You can't scare us,
you can't deter us.

01:00.260 --> 01:02.260
...by giving a voice
to the dead.

01:02.262 --> 01:04.195
I'm gonna ask you
one more time.

01:04.197 --> 01:05.697
What is your name?

01:05.699 --> 01:08.600
Because we believe the dead
and the living are all...

01:08.602 --> 01:10.602
kindred spirits.
Kindred spirits.

01:10.604 --> 01:12.938
♪♪

01:12.940 --> 01:15.340
BRUNI: Adam and I have been
called to Louisville, Kentucky,

01:15.342 --> 01:18.276
home to the infamous
Waverly Hills Sanatorium,

01:18.278 --> 01:21.346
one of the most paranormally
active locations

01:21.348 --> 01:23.748
in the entire world.

01:23.750 --> 01:25.417
Looking at that building,

01:25.419 --> 01:27.619
it is one of the most
ominous structures.

01:27.621 --> 01:29.621
and then when you think
of everything that happened

01:29.623 --> 01:33.625
in those walls, it's just...
it's overwhelming.

01:33.627 --> 01:36.027
Before the invention
of antibiotics,

01:36.029 --> 01:40.365
a respiratory illness called
tuberculosis wiped out millions.

01:40.367 --> 01:42.301
Doctors called it
"the white plague,"

01:42.303 --> 01:44.836
patients called it
a death sentence.

01:44.838 --> 01:48.307
In Jefferson County, Kentucky,
the epidemic was so bad

01:48.309 --> 01:50.242
that officials planned
to contain the disease

01:50.244 --> 01:52.311
by quarantining the sick.

01:52.313 --> 01:55.714
The rapid construction of
Waverly Hills began in 1912.

01:57.384 --> 01:58.583
BERRY: I mean,
going up this driveway,

01:58.585 --> 02:00.185
seeing where you were
going to be,

02:00.187 --> 02:03.755
possibly where you're going
to die is, like, intense.

02:05.259 --> 02:07.025
BRUNI: Desperate
to discover a cure,

02:07.027 --> 02:09.127
doctors conducted experimental

02:09.129 --> 02:11.796
and oftentimes
barbaric surgeries.

02:11.798 --> 02:15.000
The death count at Waverly Hills
ranges wildly.

02:15.002 --> 02:18.403
Some say as many as
8,000 patients died here.

02:18.405 --> 02:21.339
Others suggest more than 50,000.

02:21.341 --> 02:23.675
The hospital closed in 1961,

02:23.677 --> 02:27.145
after scientists
finally discovered a cure.

02:27.147 --> 02:28.880
You don't walk into Waverly

02:28.882 --> 02:32.084
and not have some sort
of paranormal experience.

02:32.086 --> 02:33.952
Big haunts like this,

02:33.954 --> 02:37.022
they become notorious for
the activity and for the scares.

02:37.024 --> 02:39.490
I think there are
a ton of things

02:39.492 --> 02:41.894
that will reach out to us,
because everyone wants to speak.

02:41.896 --> 02:45.097
I feel like there are people
here who are just...

02:45.099 --> 02:46.565
that may have died here
who are just here

02:46.567 --> 02:48.033
and they don't know
why they're here.

02:48.035 --> 02:52.070
It needs people like us to
come in and tell their stories,

02:52.072 --> 02:55.440
find out who is here,
and why they're here.

02:55.442 --> 02:58.510
BRUNI: Tina Mattingly
bought the property in 2001,

02:58.512 --> 03:02.313
with plans to convert
the sanatorium into a hotel.

03:02.315 --> 03:04.783
Over time, Tina became
what you might call

03:04.785 --> 03:06.451
a paranormal caretaker,

03:06.453 --> 03:09.588
but last year,
something turned aggressive.

03:09.590 --> 03:11.523
Over the years, I've dealt
with Tina Mattingly

03:11.525 --> 03:13.058
on a number of occasions.

03:13.060 --> 03:15.594
You and I have this style
of investigating

03:15.596 --> 03:18.129
that I think Tina needs
right now.

03:18.131 --> 03:22.066
She needs to find out who these
aggressive entities are,

03:22.068 --> 03:23.268
what they're doing.

03:23.270 --> 03:24.736
Yeah, like why
are they acting out?

03:24.738 --> 03:27.272
She's all about
protecting this place

03:27.274 --> 03:29.007
and protecting
its occupants.

03:29.009 --> 03:30.341
And, you know,
she and her husband

03:30.343 --> 03:32.744
had family treated here
back in the day,

03:32.746 --> 03:34.612
so she truly cares
about the spirits

03:34.614 --> 03:36.414
living here
in the afterlife.

03:36.416 --> 03:38.082
So she feels like there's
something here

03:38.084 --> 03:39.351
that needs our help.

03:39.353 --> 03:41.353
There's always something
we can do.

03:43.357 --> 03:44.756
Hi, Tina.
-BERRY: Good to see you.

03:44.758 --> 03:46.491
Good to see you.
Thanks for coming.

03:46.493 --> 03:48.160
Let's go in and talk about,
uh, what's happening here.

03:48.162 --> 03:50.161
Okay.

03:50.163 --> 03:52.698
I do think there are spirits
here that are unsettled.

03:52.700 --> 03:53.765
-BRUNI: Right.
-BERRY: Mm-hmm.

03:53.767 --> 03:54.900
They're nasty.

03:54.902 --> 03:57.568
Yeah, and there's
usually a reason.

03:57.570 --> 04:00.705
I like to think they're trying
to tell us something or they...

04:00.707 --> 04:02.641
maybe they don't realize
they're even gone

04:02.643 --> 04:04.976
or maybe they had, you know,

04:04.978 --> 04:08.447
they didn't get to finish
their life and they're angry.

04:08.449 --> 04:10.716
Well, I think those are
the ones that we kind of

04:10.718 --> 04:12.784
are attracted to, in a way,
because we kind of had

04:12.786 --> 04:16.988
this shift in
our investigative style,

04:16.990 --> 04:20.325
where we wanted
to start helping more,

04:20.327 --> 04:23.461
not just people like you,
but them.
Mm-hmm.

04:23.463 --> 04:25.664
And looking at them less
like a novelty

04:25.666 --> 04:28.066
and putting a human side to it.
-Mm-hmm. Mm-hmm.

04:28.068 --> 04:29.401
-Yeah.
-I live here.

04:29.403 --> 04:31.002
We're just learning that
the more we reach out

04:31.004 --> 04:32.871
to these entities
and learn their stories

04:32.873 --> 04:34.873
and their reasons
for being here,

04:34.875 --> 04:38.142
it helps them kind of overcome
whatever's holding them here.

04:38.144 --> 04:39.811
There is a place
on the fourth floor

04:39.813 --> 04:41.212
I would like for y'all
to go to.

04:41.214 --> 04:42.681
-Okay.
-Okay.

04:42.683 --> 04:44.416
It's one of the ones
I'm the most uncomfortable in.

04:44.418 --> 04:45.883
Something happened to me
up there.

04:45.885 --> 04:48.686
-BRUNI: How long ago was that?
-This year.

04:48.688 --> 04:49.887
There's something that,
I just think it might be

04:49.889 --> 04:52.424
something unsettled
that needs help.

04:52.426 --> 04:56.962
♪♪

04:56.964 --> 04:58.897
BERRY:
I am still so overwhelmed

04:58.899 --> 05:01.299
by the size of it

05:01.301 --> 05:04.236
and the amount of people that
would be in here at one point.

05:04.238 --> 05:05.437
Oh, gosh, yeah.

05:05.439 --> 05:07.372
It's a 180,000 square foot
building.

05:07.374 --> 05:08.573
-Yeah.
-Oh.

05:08.575 --> 05:10.041
How many people were here,
at one point?

05:10.043 --> 05:11.643
Well, you know,
it's got five floors.
Mm-hmm.

05:11.645 --> 05:13.978
-Over 500 rooms.
-BERRY: Yeah.

05:13.980 --> 05:16.381
And they took a lot
of these big atrium rooms

05:16.383 --> 05:17.516
and they would make 'em
into wards.

05:17.518 --> 05:18.850
-Mm-hmm.
-Right.

05:18.852 --> 05:20.718
And, you know,
so there's no telling

05:20.720 --> 05:23.522
how many people were in here,
at one point in time.

05:23.524 --> 05:24.990
What --
what was the death total?

05:24.992 --> 05:26.525
It's in the thousands.

05:29.062 --> 05:31.730
BRUNI: What kind of surgery
would you do for tuberculosis?

05:31.732 --> 05:33.865
TINA:
Remove lungs, remove ribs.

05:33.867 --> 05:37.135
The survival rate was,
back in that day, was about 5%.

05:37.137 --> 05:39.204
BERRY: Oh, my God.

05:39.206 --> 05:41.807
So show us where you had
your experience

05:41.809 --> 05:44.008
and kind of explain to us
what it was.

05:44.010 --> 05:45.410
Well, I've had
a lot of experiences,

05:45.412 --> 05:46.611
but this unsettled me,

05:46.613 --> 05:49.347
and I actually wanted
to leave the area.

05:49.349 --> 05:50.949
And I don't usually do that.

05:50.951 --> 05:52.084
-Right.
-Okay.

05:52.086 --> 05:53.351
It was just unnerving.

05:53.353 --> 05:54.485
Well, that's a lot
coming from you,

05:54.487 --> 05:55.687
because I feel like
you've probably

05:55.689 --> 05:58.022
had hundreds of experiences
here, at this point.

05:58.024 --> 06:00.225
I've had a lot of things,
but not too many of 'em

06:00.227 --> 06:01.893
make me feel uncomfortable.

06:01.895 --> 06:04.162
This room right here.
-BERRY: Room 424.

06:04.164 --> 06:05.564
I had about five guys
with me.

06:05.566 --> 06:07.298
They were doing
an overnight investigation

06:07.300 --> 06:09.634
with, you know, a form
of a Spirit Box.

06:09.636 --> 06:12.704
And as soon as we hit
the hallway,

06:12.706 --> 06:14.305
it was
a really bad smell.

06:14.307 --> 06:16.774
It engulfed the whole area,
the whole floor.

06:16.776 --> 06:18.376
And I just kind of
stood over here

06:18.378 --> 06:20.846
while they set everything up,

06:20.848 --> 06:23.381
and it just started going nuts.
-Mm-hmm.

06:23.383 --> 06:26.384
And, I mean, it was
screaming and yelling.

06:26.386 --> 06:28.453
And cackling, laughing,
everything.
Really?

06:28.455 --> 06:31.189
I can't even explain
what it sounded like.

06:31.191 --> 06:33.325
It sounded like you were
just in a -- in a nuthouse.

06:33.327 --> 06:34.593
-Really? Okay.
-Yeah.

06:34.595 --> 06:36.128
And as I stood here,

06:36.130 --> 06:39.331
I looked down this way,
I saw a little blue light

06:39.333 --> 06:42.667
and I watched it move,
and it started coming this way.

06:42.669 --> 06:45.270
It was only...probably no bigger
around than, like,

06:45.272 --> 06:47.005
a ping-pong ball.

06:47.007 --> 06:51.409
And when it disappeared,
that box shut up.

06:51.411 --> 06:53.812
What did it -- what,
did it sound male, female?

06:53.814 --> 06:56.948
Everything? It was just
a bunch of voices?

06:56.950 --> 06:59.951
Okay.
All right, so it was a number
of people screaming,

06:59.953 --> 07:01.152
it sounded like?
-Yes.

07:01.154 --> 07:02.553
And it was freaking
them out, too.

07:02.555 --> 07:04.155
Mm-hmm.

07:04.157 --> 07:05.623
So I took them down to the other
floor and I looked at 'em.

07:05.625 --> 07:07.625
I said, "I'm going to go back
up on the fourth floor

07:07.627 --> 07:10.294
and I'm going to see if
there's anybody else up there."

07:10.296 --> 07:12.630
And I came up the stairwell
on the other end,

07:12.632 --> 07:14.232
I'm saying,
"Is anybody up here?"

07:14.234 --> 07:16.768
and then all of a sudden,
from the right side of me,

07:16.770 --> 07:19.838
I mean, it was just
a shriek so loud,

07:19.840 --> 07:20.972
it was almost deafening.

07:20.974 --> 07:23.241
It scared me. I jumped
and I just swung around.

07:23.243 --> 07:25.243
If I can say I've actually
smacked something...

07:25.245 --> 07:26.711
-Mm-hmm.
-...I did.

07:26.713 --> 07:27.846
-That was it.
-That was it.

07:27.848 --> 07:30.047
And I just yelled,
"You stop that!"

07:30.049 --> 07:33.785
And as soon as I said that,
the smell was gone,

07:33.787 --> 07:36.588
the noise was gone,
everything was gone.

07:36.590 --> 07:38.055
Yeah, it wasn't nice.

07:38.057 --> 07:40.057
BRUNI: What did this floor
used to be?

07:40.059 --> 07:43.261
It was, uh, a mental floor,
for mental patients.

07:43.263 --> 07:46.531
-BRUNI: Ohh. Okay.
-BERRY: We have a lot to do.

07:46.533 --> 07:48.065
BRUNI: To be here for
multiple nights

07:48.067 --> 07:51.336
and really get to delve into
this place is exciting for us.

07:51.338 --> 07:54.139
TINA: There's something
there that needs help.

07:54.141 --> 07:55.874
I'm sure you'll get
some answers.

07:55.876 --> 08:00.011
BRUNI: Waverly Hills is almost
200,000 square feet.

08:00.013 --> 08:02.881
Thousands of patients died here,
and any number of them

08:02.883 --> 08:04.950
can be responsible
for the haunt.

08:04.952 --> 08:07.752
So the fact that Tina
pinpointed an aggressive entity

08:07.754 --> 08:10.555
on the fourth floor at least
gives us a starting point.

08:10.557 --> 08:11.756
Ooh.

08:11.758 --> 08:13.691
I'm a little nervous.
-I mean...Yeah.

08:13.693 --> 08:15.827
BRUNI: We're setting up cameras
in the exact area

08:15.829 --> 08:17.428
she had her encounter

08:17.430 --> 08:18.563
[ Filtered voice ]
Camera one is up.

08:20.267 --> 08:21.766
Hey, come look at this.
Watch this.

08:21.768 --> 08:23.568
Yeah. That's
like something -- Oh!

08:23.570 --> 08:25.103
What is<i> that</i> moving?

08:25.105 --> 08:26.237
See that?

08:26.239 --> 08:28.640
Yeah.
Um, is it peeking out?

08:28.642 --> 08:31.776
It's like something's pacing
right here.

08:31.778 --> 08:34.479
That's on the fourth floor.
Do you want to go up there?
Yeah.

08:36.283 --> 08:37.582
BRUNI: We're headed upstairs,

08:37.584 --> 08:39.184
where we will attempt
to make contact

08:39.186 --> 08:41.653
with the spirit
using our recorder.

08:43.790 --> 08:46.324
Don't you feel like
you're being watched?

08:46.326 --> 08:47.859
Yeah.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.661
Just have a weird feeling.

08:49.663 --> 08:58.269
♪♪

08:58.271 --> 09:00.605
-BERRY: Oh, [bleep].
-What?

09:00.607 --> 09:03.074
This floor gives me
the creeps.

09:03.076 --> 09:04.408
I know, me, too.

09:04.410 --> 09:07.412
Well, especially after
what she told us today.

09:07.414 --> 09:13.284
♪♪

09:13.286 --> 09:16.087
It's, uh, here.

09:16.089 --> 09:17.389
424?

09:22.829 --> 09:25.163
I just can't stop
staring down these halls.
I know.

09:25.165 --> 09:29.968
♪♪

09:29.970 --> 09:32.437
All right, this is where
our friend Tina said

09:32.439 --> 09:34.038
she heard some screaming.

09:34.040 --> 09:36.241
Do you need help?

09:36.243 --> 09:38.510
We help people like you.

09:38.512 --> 09:41.446
And sometimes we can find
your family.

09:41.448 --> 09:43.848
We can find your friends.

09:43.850 --> 09:45.516
Would you like that?

09:45.518 --> 09:50.588
♪♪

09:50.590 --> 09:52.123
And if you wouldn't,
that's okay, too.

09:52.125 --> 09:53.725
We don't have to find
your family and friends.

09:53.727 --> 09:56.261
If you want to just talk to us,
that's okay.

09:56.263 --> 10:03.668
♪♪

10:03.670 --> 10:05.936
Let's listen,
but it sounds quiet.

10:05.938 --> 10:07.806
-Hmm.
-It's not a lot of...

10:35.635 --> 10:37.569
Ooh!

10:39.906 --> 10:42.374
Check this out.
There was a murder.

10:42.376 --> 10:45.243
This man killed people.

10:45.245 --> 10:46.444
Stabbed.

10:46.446 --> 10:49.180
I felt like something
was all on me.

10:49.182 --> 10:50.582
♪♪

10:57.791 --> 11:02.127
♪♪

11:02.129 --> 11:04.596
BRUNI: Adam and I just
kicked off our investigation

11:04.598 --> 11:06.597
of the fourth floor
at Waverly Hills,

11:06.599 --> 11:10.535
a tuberculosis sanatorium
where thousands of people died.

11:10.537 --> 11:13.938
And we've just made contact with
a threatening entity.

11:13.940 --> 11:15.540
BERRY:<i> Do you need any help?</i>

11:15.542 --> 11:18.076
BRUNI:<i> Sometimes,</i>
<i>we can find your family.</i>

11:18.078 --> 11:19.744
<i>We can find your friends...</i>

11:27.888 --> 11:29.354
Ooh!

11:31.291 --> 11:33.158
No way.

11:33.160 --> 11:35.093
That is angry.

11:35.095 --> 11:37.495
<i>...your friends.</i>
<i>Would you like that?</i>

11:37.497 --> 11:40.965
That's surprised the hell
out of me.

11:40.967 --> 11:43.368
That's not a happy voice.

11:43.370 --> 11:44.636
<i>No!</i>

11:44.638 --> 11:46.170
<i>You want to get out of here?</i>

11:46.172 --> 11:48.038
[Bleep], no.
-[ Whispers ] No!

11:48.040 --> 11:49.440
Do not --
If you don't want

11:49.442 --> 11:51.943
to find your family
and friends, that's okay.

11:53.780 --> 11:55.180
[ Whispers ] No!

11:55.182 --> 11:57.916
<i>You want to get out?</i>
[Bleep, speaks indistinctly ]

11:59.385 --> 12:00.918
So we're in the exact spot

12:00.920 --> 12:03.454
where she heard something
scream in her ear.

12:03.456 --> 12:06.524
And something just screamed,
"No!" at us.

12:06.526 --> 12:10.061
It does not want us here.
It does not like us.

12:10.063 --> 12:11.596
-Sounds like a male.
-Mm-hmm.

12:11.598 --> 12:15.066
Why is he so mad?

12:15.068 --> 12:18.670
As soon as I heard that voice,
I got chills from head to toe.

12:18.672 --> 12:21.539
-Yep. Yep.
-He is not happy,

12:21.541 --> 12:24.409
especially when I brought up
family and friends,

12:24.411 --> 12:26.076
which makes me wonder
if he was, like,

12:26.078 --> 12:27.745
abandoned here or something.
-[ Sniffles ]

12:27.747 --> 12:30.548
You also brought up
family and friends,

12:30.550 --> 12:33.084
but you -- your words were,
"You can talk to us."

12:33.086 --> 12:35.820
-Yeah, and he did not --
-And it's like, "No!"

12:35.822 --> 12:38.622
That's the worst thing that we
could've heard tonight, I mean.

12:38.624 --> 12:40.825
That voice was not happy
with us.

12:40.827 --> 12:42.827
Something is striking a nerve.
-Yeah.

12:42.829 --> 12:47.031
I mean, that is not something
you want to hear in Waverly.

12:47.033 --> 12:50.100
BRUNI: Waverly Hills is not
the place to mess around.

12:50.102 --> 12:52.036
Many of the spirits
haunting this building

12:52.038 --> 12:55.373
feel trapped and desperate
and could be dangerous.

12:55.375 --> 12:57.708
I'm wondering if we should
call in Chip.

12:57.710 --> 12:58.977
Mm-hmm.

12:58.979 --> 13:00.445
He might be able to guide us
a little more.

13:00.447 --> 13:02.313
Find out who they are, if they
have messages to give out,

13:02.315 --> 13:04.448
if they, what they need.

13:04.450 --> 13:06.450
So maybe we could take him
to the fourth floor

13:06.452 --> 13:09.987
without telling him what
experiences we've had up there

13:09.989 --> 13:11.322
and gets his impression.

13:11.324 --> 13:12.523
Mm-hmm.

13:12.525 --> 13:14.125
BRUNI:
Before we bring in Chip,

13:14.127 --> 13:17.061
Adam and I need to know
who we are dealing with.

